		"body": "## Description\r\nThis PR resolves the line-wrap indentation misalignment in the Markdown editor. Previously, wrapped lines in lists (bullet points, checkboxes) did not align correctly under the text marker due to issues with how `text-indent` and `padding-left` interacted with tab-stops in the CodeMirror 6 editor. \r\n\r\nThis implementation ensures that the first line remains unindented, while subsequent wrapped lines have an indent that perfectly matches the width of the space/tabs plus the marker width.\r\n\r\n## Solution\r\nRefactored `CheckboxWidget` in replaceCheckboxes.ts to:\r\n1. Extract actual marker text from the markdown source \r\n2. Create a hidden `.sizing` span containing the marker text to preserve width\r\n3. Absolutely position the checkbox input over the sizing span\r\n4. Remove depth-based CSS class approximations\r\n\r\nThis ensures the checkbox input is always aligned with the actual marker width regardless of indentation level.\r\n\r\n## Testing\r\n- TypeScript compilation successful with no errors\r\n- Rendering pipeline validated (adjacent test suite passes)\r\n-  Tested in the desktop Markdown editor with tab indentation.\r\n- Tested in the desktop Markdown editor with space indentation.\r\n\r\n## Successfully Wrapped up Lines\r\n<img width=\"1919\" height=\"1099\" alt=\"Screenshot 2026-03-20 191722\" src=\"https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/20bb81b6-4102-4540-b025-6407b59c45b6\" />\r\n\r\nYou can able to all the checkboxes with so long content have been correctly wrapped up...\r\n\r\n## Related Issue\r\nFixes #12996\r\n",
